main event: A very white light was observed in the sky traveling from West to East on May 17, 1964.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 20 minutes, The light was reported to be visible to tower personnel in the area, The observation was considered a misinterpretation of a conventional object by personnel, No other lights were reported visible by nearby agencies, There was insufficient data for a definitive conclusion about the object's nature.
sighted object: very white light in the sky
witness description: tower personnel and other agencies in the area
